 ConsumerLoopCommit;start;cr;r;config;consumer;consumed_msg;commit_count;committed;last_consumed
⍝ Consumer consumes messages from two topics synchronously and commits offsets every 20 messages

 #.Init'.'

⍝ consumer configurations
 config←0 2⍴⍬
 config⍪←'bootstrap.servers' 'localhost:9092'
 config⍪←'client.id' 'consumerLclient'
 config⍪←'group.id' 'consumerLgroup'
 config⍪←'auto.offset.reset' 'earliest'
 config⍪←'enable.auto.commit' 'false'
 ⎕←'consumer configuration'
 config

⍝ Init consumer
 consumer←⎕NEW #.Consumer config

⍝ Subscribe consumer to topic
 ⎕←'Subscribe consumer on topic: topic1 and topic2'
 consumer.subscribe'topic1' 'topic2'
 ⎕←'Waiting for rebalance before starting consuming...'
 ⎕DL 5

 ⎕←'Start polling messages'
 start←3⊃⎕AI
 commit_count←20
 consumed_msg←0
 last_consumed←3⊃⎕AI
 :While 60000>(3⊃⎕AI)-last_consumed
     cr←consumer.consume_record
     :If 1=⊃cr
     :AndIf 20000>(3⊃⎕AI)-start
         :Continue
     :ElseIf 0=⊃cr
         (2⊃cr).(Topic Payload Key Partition)
         last_consumed←3⊃⎕AI
         start←0
         consumed_msg←consumed_msg+1
         committed←0
     :EndIf
     :If (~committed)∧0=commit_count|consumed_msg
         ⎕←'Commit consumer'
         consumer.commit
         committed←1
     :EndIf
 :EndWhile

 ⎕EX'consumer'
